    <para id="id1171293276658">(Adapted from ’ The Great Spectrum Famine’ by Mitchell Lazarus, Spectrum , November, 2010)</para>
    <para id="id1171291619119">Table 1. The Opportunity Window: The best frequencies for mobile broadband are high enough that the antenna can be made conveniently compact and yet not so high that it fails to penetrate the buildings. This leaves a relatively narrow range of frequencies available for use i.e. from 300MHz to 3.5GHz..</para>
